abstract={A 4F2 permanent digital archive system is presented. Data is saved by the presence of a metal nano-dot at a x-point of interconnects. This passive storage node works as a permanent memory cell with >1,000-years endurance. No transistor is used in the cell, enabling multi-layer memory stack for high-density. Mutual capacitance change due to the nano-dot presence is sensed for data retrieve. A 0/1-bit-balanced encoding enhances long-time reliability. A 0.18μm CMOS prototype successfully operates after accelerated aging (equivalent to a 1,000-years period). A 6-layer memory stack in 28nm CMOS can realize 0.4Tb/inch2 capacity.}, 
